# BOMBERMP - A 2D Multiplayer Browser based Bomber Game

## Goals:

- Create a realtime 2d multiplayer bomber game:
  
  - requiements: 
    - base game logic:
      - world will be a 2d maze like with different types of walls and obstacles
      - player will be able to move around the world
      - player will be able to drop bombs
      - bombs will be able to explode in some time
      - some walls/obstacles will be able to be destroyed by bombs
      - think of it like a pacman world but with breakable/unbreakable walls and bombs
      - walls/obstacles will have a drop rate of items
      - items will be able to be picked up by the player
      - items will be able to be used by the player
      - some items will be able to be destroyed by bombs
    
    - loot/drops system:
      - items will be able to be dropped by the player
      - items will be able to be picked up by the player
      - items will be able to be used by the player
      - some items will be able to be destroyed by bombs
      - types: 
        - pickables: 
          - max bomb additions
          - bomb damage radius 
        - traps/effects:
          - speed slowdown

    - gameplay:
      - player will join a game
      - player start to drop bombs
      - player starts to destroy walls/obstacles 
      - player starts to pick up items
      - player will be faced with other players/bots


     - singleplayer/multiplayer:
       - currently no singleplayer
       - only room based multiplayer
       - once a player joins they can create or join a room:
          - creation: 
            - player will be able to create a room
            - will get a room id / joining link
          - joining:
            - player will be able to join a room by entering the joining link/room id
            - or opening the room directly with the room link
      - max of 4 players per room
      - they can see each other in lobby
      - creator will be able to start the game when they want
      - all the players will have differnt colors based on the lobby

      - game start:
        - all player will be spawned in all corners of the room with drop rate of 1 bombs per 3 seconds
        - all player will be able to see each other
        - as per the game logic:
          - player must kill other players to win
        - once a single player is left the game will be over
        - basically last standing player wins
        - once game ends all players will again come back to the lobby

     
    - technical requiremetns:
      - gameplay should be smooth and realtime
      - currently we are only deployting this to once single region (asia-south1)
      - we will be using google cloud instances to deploy this game.
      - we will persist the users using adding a cookie to the user's browser
      - currently we are not adding any authentication
      - we will be using a websocket to communicate between the server and the client
      - for db we will be using mongodb on local docker or atlas      
      - stack: 
        - db: mongodb
        - server: nodejs, typescript, express, socket.io
        - client: typescript, html, html canvas, css, javascript, socket.io
        - deploy: google cloud
        - package manager: pnpm
        - domain: bombermb.avinashjha.space
      - structure:
        - single monorepo for 
          - server
          - client
          - shared types, models, and utils for server 
      - deployement:
        - frontend will be in the nginx server in docker container: https://bombermb.avinashjha.space
        - backend will be in another container proxied by nginx container at: https://bombermbapi.avinashjha.space or wss://bombermbapi.avinashjha.space

    - other requiremetns:
      - user should be able to see the stats of network latency of thier and others
      - higher latency should be shown properly
